  "prompt": "What does the Chinese word \u300c\u6c14\u8d28\u300dmean?",
  "response": "The Chinese word \u300c\u6c14\u8d28\u300d (pinyin: *q\u00ec zh\u00ec*) refers to a person's **temperament**, **disposition**, or **natural qualities** that shape their behavior, demeanor, and overall presence. It encompasses both **internal characteristics** (such as personality traits and emotional tendencies) and the **external manifestation** of these traits (like posture, style, and mannerisms).\n\n### Breakdown of the Term:\n- **\u6c14 (q\u00ec):** Often translated as \"energy,\" \"spirit,\" or \"breath,\" it relates to the vital force or essence within a person.\n- **\u8d28 (zh\u00ec):** Means \"quality,\" \"nature,\" or \"substance,\" referring to the inherent characteristics of someone or something.\n\nWhen combined, \u300c\u6c14\u8d28\u300d conveys the unique blend of a person's inner qualities and how these are outwardly expressed, contributing to their distinctive presence.\n\n### Usage Examples:\n1. **\u5979\u7684\u6c14\u8d28\u975e\u5e38\u4f18\u96c5\uff0c\u603b\u662f\u7ed9\u4eba\u4e00\u79cd\u9ad8\u8d35\u7684\u611f\u89c9\u3002**\n   \n   *T\u0101 de q\u00ec zh\u00ec f\u0113ich\u00e1ng y\u014duy\u01ce, z\u01d2ng sh\u00ec g\u011bi r\u00e9n y\u012b zh\u01d2ng g\u0101ogu\u00ec de g\u01cenju\u00e9.*\n\n   *Her temperament is very elegant, always giving people a noble impression.*\n\n2. **\u4e0d\u540c\u7684\u73af\u5883\u53ef\u4ee5\u5f71\u54cd\u4e00\u4e2a\u4eba\u7684\u6c14\u8d28\u53d1\u5c55\u3002**\n   \n   *B\u00f9t\u00f3ng de hu\u00e1nj\u00ecng k\u011by\u01d0 y\u01d0ngxi\u01ceng y\u012bg\u00e8 r\u00e9n de q\u00ec zh\u00ec f\u0101zh\u01cen.*\n\n   *Different environments can influence the development of a person's temperament.*\n\n3. **\u4ed6\u62e5\u6709\u9886\u5bfc\u8005\u7684\u6c14\u8d28\uff0c\u5584\u4e8e\u6fc0\u52b1\u56e2\u961f\u3002**\n   \n   *T\u0101 y\u014dngy\u01d2u l\u01d0ngd\u01ceozh\u011b de q\u00ec zh\u00ec, sh\u00e0ny\u00fa j\u012bl\u00ec tu\u00e1ndu\u00ec.*\n\n   *He possesses the qualities of a leader, good at motivating the team.*\n\n### Cultural Context:\nIn Chinese culture, \u300c\u6c14\u8d28\u300d is often valued as it reflects the harmony and balance within an individual. It's associated with concepts like **\u5185\u5916\u517c\u4fee** (*n\u00e8i w\u00e0i ji\u0101n xi\u016b*)\u2014cultivating both internal virtues and external manners\u2014and is considered an important aspect in personal relationships, professional settings, and social interactions.\n\nUnderstanding someone's \u300c\u6c14\u8d28\u300d can provide insights into their behavior, preferences, and how they might interact with others, making it a significant term in both personal assessments and literary descriptions.",
